HEADWORD: Corrivate
<hw>Cor"ri*vate</hw> <pr>(k?r"r?-v?t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>corrivatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>corrivare</ets> to
corrivate.]</ety> <def>To cause to flow together, as water drawn from
several streams.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

